# -*- encoding: utf-8 -*-
# Arc: SailorArc | Scene: SarahLeavesLethram1
# Source: C:\Program Files (x86)\Steam\steamapps\common\The Survival of Sarah Rose\game\script.rpy

translate ru strings:

    old "Sarah kept to the main road."
    new "Sarah kept to the main road."

    old "All around her, she could see the city coming to life, its countless citizens spilling out from their homes to start their day."
    new "All around her, she could see the city coming to life, its countless citizens spilling out from their homes to start their day."

    old "Sarah had grown up in Castle Reinmeer, only rarely venturing much further than the capital of Rosanna."
    new "Sarah had grown up in Castle Reinmeer, only rarely venturing much further than the capital of Rosanna."

    old "It still surprised her just how large the world was. How many millions of people lived out their lives, each sparing her nation as much a thought as she had previously spared their city."
    new "It still surprised her just how large the world was. How many millions of people lived out their lives, each sparing her nation as much a thought as she had previously spared their city."

    old "She mingled in with the growing crowd, contuining up the busy main road."
    new "She mingled in with the growing crowd, contuining up the busy main road."

    old "Lethram was dangerous, certainly to a young woman with few allies or ways of protecting herself."
    new "Lethram was dangerous, certainly to a young woman with few allies or ways of protecting herself."

    old "Despite this, Sarah felt an odd comfort in the masses of people."
    new "Despite this, Sarah felt an odd comfort in the masses of people."

    old "Nobody spared her any attention, neither good nor ill. After having survived a harrowing night, being left alone seemed almost like a blessing."
    new "Nobody spared her any attention, neither good nor ill. After having survived a harrowing night, being left alone seemed almost like a blessing."

    old "The further Sarah went up the road, the more the air itself seemed to change."
    new "The further Sarah went up the road, the more the air itself seemed to change."

    old "Lethram was a port city. As a result, the air in most of the city was infected with a sharp salty smell, carried in by the wind currents."
    new "Lethram was a port city. As a result, the air in most of the city was infected with a sharp salty smell, carried in by the wind currents."

    old "With each step, Sarah could smell the air turn increasingly familiar, more to the kind she was used to back in Rosanna."
    new "With each step, Sarah could smell the air turn increasingly familiar, more to the kind she was used to back in Rosanna."

    old "She was surpised to realise how it soothed her."
    new "She was surpised to realise how it soothed her."

    old "Around her, the crowds slowly thinned out."
    new "Around her, the crowds slowly thinned out."

    old "With most of the economy focussed around the port district, the upper parts of the city were left more sparse."
    new "With most of the economy focussed around the port district, the upper parts of the city were left more sparse."

    old "Less trade. Fewer businesses. Fewer reasons for much of anyone to be here."
    new "Less trade. Fewer businesses. Fewer reasons for much of anyone to be here."

    old "It was here, after nearly an hour of walking, that Sarah finally came upon the city gates of Lethram."
    new "It was here, after nearly an hour of walking, that Sarah finally came upon the city gates of Lethram."

    old "The city gates of Lethram were build more like the fortresses back in Rosanna."
    new "The city gates of Lethram were build more like the fortresses back in Rosanna."

    old "Solid blocks, rows of metal gates, and heavy artillery placements."
    new "Solid blocks, rows of metal gates, and heavy artillery placements."

    old "Lethram did not rely on sea trade simply because the city wanted to. In many ways, the city relied on sea trade because it had to."
    new "Lethram did not rely on sea trade simply because the city wanted to. In many ways, the city relied on sea trade because it had to."

    old "The city was an oasis of civilization in what was otherwise a large tract of land that was in constant conflict and strife."
    new "The city was an oasis of civilization in what was otherwise a large tract of land that was in constant conflict and strife."

    old "This was why the city gates of Lethram were build the way they were."
    new "This was why the city gates of Lethram were build the way they were."

    old "They were not build to welcome trade from the outside. They were build to resist the only thing Lethram expected from the hinterlands, an attack."
    new "They were not build to welcome trade from the outside. They were build to resist the only thing Lethram expected from the hinterlands, an attack."

    old "Looking on the bulwark and its many weaponry, and heavily armored soldiers, Sarah wondered if anyone could be mad enough to even consider an attack."
    new "Looking on the bulwark and its many weaponry, and heavily armored soldiers, Sarah wondered if anyone could be mad enough to even consider an attack."

    old "As Sarah continued, the road converged on a landbridge, the only definitive way in or out of Lethram."
    new "As Sarah continued, the road converged on a landbridge, the only definitive way in or out of Lethram."

    old "Crossing it, Sarah for a moment expected someone might stop her, but to her surprise, nobody ever did."
    new "Crossing it, Sarah for a moment expected someone might stop her, but to her surprise, nobody ever did."

    old "The only thing she received were some confused stares."
    new "The only thing she received were some confused stares."

    old "Taking her final step out through the gate, Sarah watched as the world opened up before her."
    new "Taking her final step out through the gate, Sarah watched as the world opened up before her."

    old "The suffocating feeling inside of Lethram, with its many buildings, gave way to an almost rural surrounding."
    new "The suffocating feeling inside of Lethram, with its many buildings, gave way to an almost rural surrounding."

    old "Sarah looked out ahead of her."
    new "Sarah looked out ahead of her."

    old "The well-paved and maintained road of Lethram started to fade almost immediately."
    new "The well-paved and maintained road of Lethram started to fade almost immediately."

    old "Instead, only a rural, decaying road stretched out. A few sparse buildings remained."
    new "Instead, only a rural, decaying road stretched out. A few sparse buildings remained."

    old "Much further than that, Sarah could only see rolling hills, without so much as a soul in sight."
    new "Much further than that, Sarah could only see rolling hills, without so much as a soul in sight."

    old "For a moment she hesitated."
    new "For a moment she hesitated."

    old "The city had been dangerous, but who was to say that the world outside of the city was any better?"
    new "The city had been dangerous, but who was to say that the world outside of the city was any better?"

    old "Sarah clenched her fists."
    new "Sarah clenched her fists."

    old "Memories flashed in front of her eyes of the man who had almost attacked her in the alley."
    new "Memories flashed in front of her eyes of the man who had almost attacked her in the alley."

    old "That had been just one night."
    new "That had been just one night."

    old "Whatever was out there, surely it couldn't be worse than living on the streets of Lethram."
    new "Whatever was out there, surely it couldn't be worse than living on the streets of Lethram."

    old "She forced herself to walk forward, following the decaying road."
    new "She forced herself to walk forward, following the decaying road."

    old "Five steps were all she could take before a voice rang out."
    new "Five steps were all she could take before a voice rang out."

    old "Are you out of your damned mind, girl?"
    new "Are you out of your damned mind, girl?"

    old "Sarah instinctively turned around towards the voice."
    new "Sarah instinctively turned around towards the voice."

    old "Sarah nearly fell over backwards as she tried to back away from the hulking man that now approached her."
    new "Sarah nearly fell over backwards as she tried to back away from the hulking man that now approached her."

    old "His eyes seemed to shoot fire."
    new "His eyes seemed to shoot fire."

    old "I asked you if you've lost your mind!"
    new "I asked you if you've lost your mind!"

    old "Sarah struggled to find her voice."
    new "Sarah struggled to find her voice."

    old "I...what did I..."
    new "I...what did I..."

    old "The man came up to her, only a few feet away."
    new "The man came up to her, only a few feet away."

    old "He had an old, worn face, but his age seemed hard to estimate given his muscular build and broad shoulders, making him seem younger than he otherwise was."
    new "He had an old, worn face, but his age seemed hard to estimate given his muscular build and broad shoulders, making him seem younger than he otherwise was."

    old "For a moment, the man seemed to calm down."
    new "For a moment, the man seemed to calm down."

    old "Tell me, girl, why are you out here?"
    new "Tell me, girl, why are you out here?"

    old "Still struggling for words, Sarah decided to simply speak the truth."
    new "Still struggling for words, Sarah decided to simply speak the truth."

    old "I was...I was leaving Lethram. I'm heading out down the road to find...a place that I can stay."
    new "I was...I was leaving Lethram. I'm heading out down the road to find...a place that I can stay."

    old "She saw the man rubbing his temples, frustrated."
    new "She saw the man rubbing his temples, frustrated."

    old "This place is dangerous enough for just about anybody, girl."
    new "This place is dangerous enough for just about anybody, girl."

    old "Someone like you wouldn't last a day out on the old road."
    new "Someone like you wouldn't last a day out on the old road."

    old "I don't want to find your corpse in some ditch, your throat slashed by some bandit."
    new "I don't want to find your corpse in some ditch, your throat slashed by some bandit."

    old "Go back to the city, you'll be a lot safer there."
    new "Go back to the city, you'll be a lot safer there."

    old "Sarah felt like crying."
    new "Sarah felt like crying."

    old "She had only just managed to find the courage to leave Lethram, and now this stranger was all but forcing her back."
    new "She had only just managed to find the courage to leave Lethram, and now this stranger was all but forcing her back."

    old "Sarah forced herself to speak through the sobs."
    new "Sarah forced herself to speak through the sobs."

    old "I was in that damned city!"
    new "I was in that damned city!"

    old "And it nearly cost me my life!"
    new "And it nearly cost me my life!"

    old "You talk about bandits out here? Some lowlife nearly killed me last night. There isn't anywhere in that city that's safe."
    new "You talk about bandits out here? Some lowlife nearly killed me last night. There isn't anywhere in that city that's safe."

    old "Look, girl, I'll grant you Lethram ain't the safest place in the world, but trust me, whatever is out here is a hundred times worse."
    new "Look, girl, I'll grant you Lethram ain't the safest place in the world, but trust me, whatever is out here is a hundred times worse."

    old "Worse than Lethram. Sarah struggled to believe that could be."
    new "Worse than Lethram. Sarah struggled to believe that could be."

    old "I go back into that city and sleep on the streets till that bastard, or someone like him, finds me?"
    new "I go back into that city and sleep on the streets till that bastard, or someone like him, finds me?"

    old "She watched as the man struggled to find an answer."
    new "She watched as the man struggled to find an answer."

    old "Look. You're still young."
    new "Look. You're still young."

    old "Whatever this is, just go back home and apologize to your parents, you don't want to be out here."
    new "Whatever this is, just go back home and apologize to your parents, you don't want to be out here."

    old "I don't have any parents!"
    new "I don't have any parents!"

    old "Sarah nearly screamed the words. Who was he to make assumptions about her life?"
    new "Sarah nearly screamed the words. Who was he to make assumptions about her life?"

    old "For a moment, the words stunned the man to silence."
    new "For a moment, the words stunned the man to silence."

    old "I'm...sorry. I shouldn't have assumed."
    new "I'm...sorry. I shouldn't have assumed."

    old "But you still can't be out here. It's too dangerous."
    new "But you still can't be out here. It's too dangerous."

    old "Sarah planted her feet on the ground, as if expecting that he might try to physically force her back into the city."
    new "Sarah planted her feet on the ground, as if expecting that he might try to physically force her back into the city."

    old "I'm not going back into that city, no matter what you try."
    new "I'm not going back into that city, no matter what you try."

    old "The man sighed again. He seemed equally frustrated but equally unable to walk away and let her be."
    new "The man sighed again. He seemed equally frustrated but equally unable to walk away and let her be."

    old "I'll tell you what."
    new "I'll tell you what."

    old "There is a small farming town about a day's ride up the old road, called Gallow Creek."
    new "There is a small farming town about a day's ride up the old road, called Gallow Creek."

    old "If you absolutely don't want to go back to the city, me and my men can take you there."
    new "If you absolutely don't want to go back to the city, me and my men can take you there."

    old "It's a small community, but they're good people. You'll be safe there."
    new "It's a small community, but they're good people. You'll be safe there."

    old "Sarah listened to the man speak."
    new "Sarah listened to the man speak."

    old "It had sounded like the kind of place she wanted to go."
    new "It had sounded like the kind of place she wanted to go."

    old "A place with decent people. No criminals roaming every street corner. A place where she could gather her thoughts and plan."
    new "A place with decent people. No criminals roaming every street corner. A place where she could gather her thoughts and plan."

    old "I'll accept your offer."
    new "I'll accept your offer."

    old "The man chuckled."
    new "The man chuckled."

    old "You're taking me, a total stranger, up on a ride to a town you don't even know is real?"
    new "You're taking me, a total stranger, up on a ride to a town you don't even know is real?"

    old "It's not real?"
    new "It's not real?"

    old "It is real. I just mean you're lucky that you ran into me."
    new "It is real. I just mean you're lucky that you ran into me."

    old "Just about every other bastard on the old road would have taken you two miles up the road, robbed you and left you behind, or worse."
    new "Just about every other bastard on the old road would have taken you two miles up the road, robbed you and left you behind, or worse."

    old "You're too naive for city life, hell you might be too naive for small town life."
    new "You're too naive for city life, hell you might be too naive for small town life."

    old "You really shouldn't be out here."
    new "You really shouldn't be out here."

    old "Well, I ain't going anywhere else."
    new "Well, I ain't going anywhere else."

    old "You got a spark to you, I'll give you that."
    new "You got a spark to you, I'll give you that."

    old "The man extended his hand to her."
    new "The man extended his hand to her."

    old "My name is Sigmund by the way, best you know my name before you get on my cart."
    new "My name is Sigmund by the way, best you know my name before you get on my cart."

    old "Sarah took his hand."
    new "Sarah took his hand."

    old "It was large enough that his hand nearly enveloped hers."
    new "It was large enough that his hand nearly enveloped hers."

    old "Sarah, nice to meet you."
    new "Sarah, nice to meet you."

    old "Nice to meet you too, Sarah."
    new "Nice to meet you too, Sarah."

    old "Come along, follow me. My cart is just over there."
    new "Come along, follow me. My cart is just over there."

    old "Sarah followed the man. She could see his cart from a distance."
    new "Sarah followed the man. She could see his cart from a distance."

    old "Two men were sitting up against the wheels, sitting in the shade of the cart, hiding from the sun."
    new "Two men were sitting up against the wheels, sitting in the shade of the cart, hiding from the sun."

    old "As they came closer, the two men got to their feet, having noticed her and Sigmund approach."
    new "As they came closer, the two men got to their feet, having noticed her and Sigmund approach."

    old "Sakar, Krip. We're taking a straggler along for a ride up to Gallow Creek."
    new "Sakar, Krip. We're taking a straggler along for a ride up to Gallow Creek."

    old "Sarah watched the smaller of the two men step forward."
    new "Sarah watched the smaller of the two men step forward."

    old "We in the business of giving out free rides now?"
    new "We in the business of giving out free rides now?"

    old "We're in the business of whatever I say we are."
    new "We're in the business of whatever I say we are."

    old "Sarah, this man here is Sakar. He's a mean bastard, so just try to ignore whatever shit comes out of his mouth."
    new "Sarah, this man here is Sakar. He's a mean bastard, so just try to ignore whatever shit comes out of his mouth."

    old "The man named Sakar laughed at his own introduction."
    new "The man named Sakar laughed at his own introduction."

    old "And Sigmund over here loves pretending to be better than he is."
    new "And Sigmund over here loves pretending to be better than he is."

    old "Don't let him charm you, he's as much a bastard as the rest of us."
    new "Don't let him charm you, he's as much a bastard as the rest of us."

    old "Ignoring the retort, Sigmund waved his hand towards the other man."
    new "Ignoring the retort, Sigmund waved his hand towards the other man."

    old "This is Krip. He isn't much for talking, but he swings an axe harder than any man I ever met, and out here on the old road that matters more than nice words."
    new "This is Krip. He isn't much for talking, but he swings an axe harder than any man I ever met, and out here on the old road that matters more than nice words."

    old "Sarah watched as the fat man made a small bow, or something that had to pass for one."
    new "Sarah watched as the fat man made a small bow, or something that had to pass for one."

    old "Just as Sigmund had said, the man wasn't much for talking and said nothing else."
    new "Just as Sigmund had said, the man wasn't much for talking and said nothing else."

    old "Eying them all, Sarah could see the men had all lived rough lives."
    new "Eying them all, Sarah could see the men had all lived rough lives."

    old "Each had a strong build, and the elements had left their mark on each of their faces."
    new "Each had a strong build, and the elements had left their mark on each of their faces."

    old "In addition to the elements, there were also the marks of violence, scars, drawn across their face and necks."
    new "In addition to the elements, there were also the marks of violence, scars, drawn across their face and necks."

    old "She instantly knew each of these men had known violence, one way or another."
    new "She instantly knew each of these men had known violence, one way or another."

    old "A pleasure to meet all of you."
    new "A pleasure to meet all of you."

    old "And I want to thank you for offering to bring me up the road."
    new "And I want to thank you for offering to bring me up the road."

    old "Sakar chuckled."
    new "Sakar chuckled."

    old "You're lucky Sigmund over here bothered to stop you."
    new "You're lucky Sigmund over here bothered to stop you."

    old "A girl like you wouldn't last a day on the old road by yourself."
    new "A girl like you wouldn't last a day on the old road by yourself."

    old "Sarah watched as the man's eyes lingered on her. She wasn't sure if he was warning her or threatening her."
    new "Sarah watched as the man's eyes lingered on her. She wasn't sure if he was warning her or threatening her."

    old "Yes, Sigmund told me it's a dangerous place."
    new "Yes, Sigmund told me it's a dangerous place."

    old "All the more reason why I am so thankful that you are willing to keep me safe."
    new "All the more reason why I am so thankful that you are willing to keep me safe."

    old "Sigmund stepped forward."
    new "Sigmund stepped forward."

    old "Right, enough pleasantries."
    new "Right, enough pleasantries."

    old "Rig up the horses, I don't wanna waste more time picking up strays!"
    new "Rig up the horses, I don't wanna waste more time picking up strays!"

    old "At his command, Sarah could see Sakar and Krip jump into action."
    new "At his command, Sarah could see Sakar and Krip jump into action."

    old "Sarah watched them busily work around the cart, pulling on ropes, tying down crates."
    new "Sarah watched them busily work around the cart, pulling on ropes, tying down crates."

    old "It seemed complicated, but the men made it look easy. As though they had done it a hundred times over."
    new "It seemed complicated, but the men made it look easy. As though they had done it a hundred times over."

    old "You get up front and ride with me, Sarah."
    new "You get up front and ride with me, Sarah."

    old "Sakar and Krip can ride on back."
    new "Sakar and Krip can ride on back."

    old "Sarah nodded and followed Sigmund's instructions, climbing onto the front of the cart."
    new "Sarah nodded and followed Sigmund's instructions, climbing onto the front of the cart."

    old "Sitting atop the elevated position, Sarah could see a bit further out."
    new "Sitting atop the elevated position, Sarah could see a bit further out."

    old "Next to her were the reins, connected to two large black horses that were standing ready, casually swatting away flies."
    new "Next to her were the reins, connected to two large black horses that were standing ready, casually swatting away flies."

    old "A large yoke bound the two animals to the wooden pulls."
    new "A large yoke bound the two animals to the wooden pulls."

    old "Growing up in Rosanna as a noble woman, Sarah was not unfamiliar with horses."
    new "Growing up in Rosanna as a noble woman, Sarah was not unfamiliar with horses."

    old "But these were clearly different from the breeds she had grown up with."
    new "But these were clearly different from the breeds she had grown up with."

    old "The kind of horses she was most familiar with were riding horses. These horses were clearly bred for burden, large and bulky, strong enough to seemingly pull anything."
    new "The kind of horses she was most familiar with were riding horses. These horses were clearly bred for burden, large and bulky, strong enough to seemingly pull anything."

    old "Around her, Sarah could see and hear that the others were busy preparing the cart for departure."
    new "Around her, Sarah could see and hear that the others were busy preparing the cart for departure."

    old "She felt guilty just sitting here, doing nothing, but she also didn't really know how she could possibly help them out."
    new "She felt guilty just sitting here, doing nothing, but she also didn't really know how she could possibly help them out."

    old "She would probably just get in the way."
    new "She would probably just get in the way."

    old "Sitting atop the box, Sarah's eyes trailed the winding road that led away from Lethram."
    new "Sitting atop the box, Sarah's eyes trailed the winding road that led away from Lethram."

    old "She couldn't see a soul."
    new "She couldn't see a soul."

    old "After a while, Sarah felt the wagon shake."
    new "After a while, Sarah felt the wagon shake."

    old "Looking off to her side, she saw Sigmund step onto the box, taking his seat besides her."
    new "Looking off to her side, she saw Sigmund step onto the box, taking his seat besides her."

    old "He grabbed the reins."
    new "He grabbed the reins."

    old "Be sure to hold onto something."
    new "Be sure to hold onto something."

    old "Sarah nervously gripped the edge of the cart's seat."
    new "Sarah nervously gripped the edge of the cart's seat."

    old "Hyaa!"
    new "Hyaa!"

    old "With a firm yell and a snapping of the reins, Sigmund forced the horses into motion."
    new "With a firm yell and a snapping of the reins, Sigmund forced the horses into motion."

    old "Sarah felt the cart begin to rock and was glad that she had chosen to hold onto something."
    new "Sarah felt the cart begin to rock and was glad that she had chosen to hold onto something."

    old "After a few more shocks, the horses finally found their speed."
    new "After a few more shocks, the horses finally found their speed."

    old "The cart's violent shaking slowly became more something like the motions of a ship, a constant back and forth."
    new "The cart's violent shaking slowly became more something like the motions of a ship, a constant back and forth."

    old "As the horses pulled the cart along the road, Sarah watched the few buildings that remained quickly fade away."
    new "As the horses pulled the cart along the road, Sarah watched the few buildings that remained quickly fade away."

    old "Before long, there was nothing but an empty road that stretched out ahead of her."
    new "Before long, there was nothing but an empty road that stretched out ahead of her."

    old "Off to the sides of the road, there was nothing more than open fields, stretching out in every direction."
    new "Off to the sides of the road, there was nothing more than open fields, stretching out in every direction."

    old "Sarah struggled to get used to it. Only a few miles out from Lethram, and nature seemed to have taken over entirely."
    new "Sarah struggled to get used to it. Only a few miles out from Lethram, and nature seemed to have taken over entirely."

    old "It's so peaceful..."
    new "It's so peaceful..."

    old "Sigmuned laughed."
    new "Sigmuned laughed."

    old "Yeah, we're still close to Lethram, but the further we get out from the city, the bolder the bandits tend to get."
    new "Yeah, we're still close to Lethram, but the further we get out from the city, the bolder the bandits tend to get."

    old "Up till Gallow's Creek nobody will mess with a cart like ours, but further up along the old road, there is no telling what can happen."
    new "Up till Gallow's Creek nobody will mess with a cart like ours, but further up along the old road, there is no telling what can happen."

    old "Sarah looked at Sigmund."
    new "Sarah looked at Sigmund."

    old "His face was rugged and a stern expression didn't do him many favors."
    new "His face was rugged and a stern expression didn't do him many favors."

    old "But there was something in his face that Sarah seemed to recognize, though she couldn't quite put her finger on it."
    new "But there was something in his face that Sarah seemed to recognize, though she couldn't quite put her finger on it."

    old "You've said that a few times now...what is that? The old road?"
    new "You've said that a few times now...what is that? The old road?"

    old "Sigmund laughed."
    new "Sigmund laughed."

    old "You're not from Lethram, are you?"
    new "You're not from Lethram, are you?"

    old "Sorry, I've been out here so long that I can end up forgetting that not everybody grew up on this side of the world."
    new "Sorry, I've been out here so long that I can end up forgetting that not everybody grew up on this side of the world."

    old "The old road is the road that stretches out from Lethram to Rahayal, the capital of Mythra."
    new "The old road is the road that stretches out from Lethram to Rahayal, the capital of Mythra."

    old "It's the only land route that still exists...somewhat."
    new "It's the only land route that still exists...somewhat."

    old "Sarah had studied enough geography growing up in Rosanna that she knew Lethram and Rahayal were on the same side of the continent, so a land route had seemed obvious to her."
    new "Sarah had studied enough geography growing up in Rosanna that she knew Lethram and Rahayal were on the same side of the continent, so a land route had seemed obvious to her."

    old "Back in Rosanna, all the union kingdoms were intertwined, and land trade made up most of the economy."
    new "Back in Rosanna, all the union kingdoms were intertwined, and land trade made up most of the economy."

    old "Why is it called the old road?"
    new "Why is it called the old road?"

    old "It's a long story, but it used to be simply called the imperial road."
    new "It's a long story, but it used to be simply called the imperial road."

    old "But after the wars of the central kingdoms, it became too dangerous for most merchants too keep using it."
    new "But after the wars of the central kingdoms, it became too dangerous for most merchants too keep using it."

    old "Seeking a safer passage, most merchants began to rely on sea routes, and Lethram given its location was more than happy to encourage that."
    new "Seeking a safer passage, most merchants began to rely on sea routes, and Lethram given its location was more than happy to encourage that."

    old "And now...I think it's been more than a century since this road has seen any real trade."
    new "And now...I think it's been more than a century since this road has seen any real trade."

    old "Now people just call it the old road."
    new "Now people just call it the old road."

    old "Sarah listend quietly."
    new "Sarah listend quietly."

    old "She thought she had been well educated, and compared to most she had been, but there was still so much of the world beyond her home country that was new and strange to her."
    new "She thought she had been well educated, and compared to most she had been, but there was still so much of the world beyond her home country that was new and strange to her."

